name: scljet-sql-where-like
description: SclJet SQL WHERE LIKE / NOT LIKE — %/_ wildcards, ASCII case-insensitive, numeric coercion, matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL WHERE LIKE / NOT LIKE

`col LIKE pattern` / `col NOT LIKE pattern`: `%` matches any run (including empty), `_` matches one
character; matching is ASCII case-insensitive (`'Ann' LIKE 'ANN'`), and a non-text column is coerced
to its text form (`dept LIKE '1%'` matches 10, 100). LIKE is a single predicate, so it composes with
`AND`/`OR`. Every result is byte-identical to reference sqlite3 running the same SQL on the same file
(verified out-of-band); locked here across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "emp", "CREATE TABLE emp(id INTEGER, name TEXT, dept INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("Ann"), SqlInteger(10L)),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("bob"), SqlInteger(20L)),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("Cat"), SqlInteger(100L)),
       List(SqlInteger(4L), SqlText("anna"), SqlInteger(10L)),
       List(SqlInteger(5L), SqlText("dan"), SqlInteger(30L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    show(db, "SELECT name FROM emp WHERE name LIKE 'a%'")
    show(db, "SELECT name FROM emp WHERE name LIKE '_a%'")
    show(db, "SELECT name FROM emp WHERE name LIKE '%n'")
    show(db, "SELECT name FROM emp WHERE name NOT LIKE 'a%'")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM emp WHERE dept LIKE '1%'")
    show(db, "SELECT name FROM emp WHERE name LIKE 'ANN'")
    show(db, "SELECT name FROM emp WHERE name LIKE 'a%' AND dept = 10")
```
